title: Roses see weak demand as prices bite
byline: Florists along Ven. Baddegama Wimalawansa Mawatha in Town Hall, Colombo said Valentine’s Day flower sales have dropped this year compared to previous years, mainly due to high prices and low consumer spending.

title: Valentine’s Day spending remains strong, nearly two thirds plan to celebrate -  Sparkwinn Research
byline: Valentine’s Day in Sri Lanka has steadily grown from a niche celebration to a notable cultural and commercial event, particularly in urban centers. Young adults increasingly embrace it as an opportunity to

title: Supreme Court says no further relief possible in Uma Oya case
byline: The Supreme Court has ruled that there is no further relief the government can provide in relation to the Uma Oya Multipurpose Development Project, stating that it is pointless to continue the case.

title: ICAO Asia-Pacific regional director arrives in Sri Lanka on state visit
byline: Mr. Tao Ma, Regional Director for Asia and the Pacific of the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO), arrived at Bandaranaike International Airport (BIA) last night (12), on a State visit to Sri Lanka.

title: Transact in Rupees, not foreign currency: CBSL warns local businesses and consumers
byline: The Central Bank yesterday issued a strong warning to businesses and consumers over the growing use of foreign currency for domestic payments, asserting such transactions are illegal and punishable by heavy

title: Recovery held firm as US$ 4.1 bn cyclone hit economy: Govt. tells bondholders
byline: Sri Lanka told international bondholders on Wednesday that a US$ 4.1 billion cyclone disaster has become the first major climate stress test of its post-default recovery, as the government seeks to reassure

title: Vouchers to purchase school shoes; validity period extended
byline: The validity period of Rs. 3,000 vouchers issued to selected schoolchildren, Piriven students and Seela Mathas for the purchase of shoes in 2026 has been extended.

title: India-Pakistan: Hottest ticket in cricket sparks T20 World Cup fever
byline: Excitement was hitting fever pitch in Colombo and across South Asia on Friday after Pakistan relented and decided to play against India in the T20 World Cup, reigniting the most lucrative match in cricket.

title: Former Maldivian President says Green Growth Plan for Sri Lanka now under review
byline: Mohamed Nasheed, former President of the Maldives and a globally recognized climate advocate, said the Climate Vulnerable Forum (CVF) created a Climate Prosperity Plan for Sri Lanka, which is now under review by the new government.

title: T20 Crisis: Australia must beat Sri Lanka or face exit
byline: Australia’s T20 World Cup hopes hang by a thread after a shocking 23-run loss to Zimbabwe in Colombo — extending their winless streak against the African side in T20 World Cups.

title: US, Taiwan finalise deal to cut tariffs, boost purchases of US goods
byline: Trump administration officials signed a final reciprocal trade agreement that confirmed a 15% U.S. tariff rate for imports from Taiwan, while committing Taiwan to a schedule for eliminating or lowering tariffs on nearly all U.S. goods.

title: National Hospital officials remanded over Rs. 50,000 bribery allegation
byline: An Acting Minor Staff Supervisor of the National Hospital in Colombo and a Health Labourer attached to the same division were ordered to be remanded till February 24 by Colombo Chief Magistrate Asanga S. Bodaragama in connection with an alleged bribery incident involving Rs. 50,000.

title: Two shot dead in Akuregoda
byline: Two persons, including a woman, were shot dead in Akuregoda a short while ago, police said.

title: Fishermen call off nine-day Satyagraha
byline: The Satyagraha campaign launched by a group of fishermen demanding the lifting of the government’s ban on the use of tractor-mounted winches for Madel (seine net) fishing was called off this evening (13).

title: Jana Aragalaya Alliance signals appeals in Amarakeerthi case
byline: The Jana Aragalaya Alliance said appeals are expected against the death sentences for 12 accused in the killing of former MP Amarakeerthi Athukorala and his security officer.

title: Fund raising scam using Energy Minister’s photo: Ministry warns
byline: The Ministry of Energy warned that a fraudulent fund-raising campaign has been reported using a fake WhatsApp number featuring a photograph of Minister Kumara Jayakody to solicit money.

title: Minister Anura Karunathilaka resigns from Committee probing release of 323 containers
byline: Minister of Ports and Civil Aviation Anura Karunathilaka has resigned from the Select Committee of Parliament to look into and report to Parliament on the release of 323 containers from the Port of Colombo without undergoing mandatory physical inspection and submit its proposals and recommendations.

title: President congratulates Tarique Rahman on Bangladesh election victory
byline: President Anura Kumara Dissanayake extended his best wishes to the people of Bangladesh for reaffirming their faith in democracy and congratulated Tarique Rahman on leading the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) in these elections.

title: Johnston Fernando, sons further remanded
byline: Former Minister Johnston Fernando and his two sons were among five suspects further remanded until February 20 by the Wattala Magistrate’s Court following their arrest by the Financial Crimes Investigation Division (FCID).

title: National ID confirmation letters issued at DRP offices this Saturday for O/L candidates
byline: The Department of Registration of Persons has announced that its Head Office and Provincial Offices in Galle, Kurunegala, Vavuniya, Batticaloa, and Nuwara Eliya will operate from 8:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. on Saturday, (14).

title: First phase of 2026 school term ends today
byline: The first phase of the first school term for 2026 concluded today (13), the Ministry of Education announced.

title: 2.5% tax on imported vehicles to take effect from April 1
byline: The Vehicle Importers’ Association of Sri Lanka (VIASL) has announced that a 2.5% tax will be imposed on imported vehicles starting from April 1, 2026.

title: Zimbabwe stun Australia with historic upset in Colombo
byline: Zimbabwe produced the first major shock of the T20 World Cup 2026, defeating former champions Australia by 23 runs at the R. Premadasa Stadium in Colombo.

title: Waruna Sri Dhanapala appointed Secretary to Ministry of Digital Economy
byline: Waruna Sri Dhanapala has been appointed as the Secretary to the Ministry of Digital Economy by President Anura Kumara Dissanayake.

title: Keheliya Rambukwella’s illicit assets case fixed for trial on April 27
byline: The Bribery Commission’s case filed against former Health Minister Keheliya Rambukwella and members of his family over allegations of illicitly accumulating assets was today fixed for trial on April 27 by Colombo High Court Judge Mohamed Mihal.

title: Month-long temporary ordination programme open at Theravada temple in Thailand
byline: An opportunity has been announced for both men and women to receive temporary ordination for the entire month of Esala at a renowned Theravada Buddhist temple in Thailand, Venerable Avissawella Dhammananda Thera said.

title: Committee on High Posts approves four Heads of Mission
byline: The Committee on High Posts of Parliament approved the nominations of four Heads of Mission.

title: Two arrested in Kandy for running fake Australia job visa scam
byline: Two youths operating a fraudulent visa consultancy centre under the pretext of offering employment opportunities in Australia were arrested yesterday (12) by officers of the Special Investigation Unit of the Sri Lanka Bureau of Foreign Employment in the Kandy area.

title: Low pressure area likely over Bay of Bengal: Met Department warns
byline: A low pressure area is likely to develop over the Bay of Bengal around February 15, the Department of Meteorology warned today.

title: Woman killed in  elephant rampage at Valaichchenai
byline: A 68-year-old woman was killed and three others injured after two wild elephants stormed into the Valaichchenai town in Batticaloa early this morning.

title: Immigration Department restores services after system glitch
byline: The technical fault in its computer system has been fully rectified, and all services have now resumed as normal, the  Immigration and Emigration Department announced.

title: Ex-Pakistan PM Imran Khan left with 15% vision in right eye, court told
byline: A court-appointed lawyer has claimed that jailed former Prime Minister Imran Khan has been left with just 15 percent vision in his right eye after authorities allegedly ignored his complaints for three months, adding another layer of contention over his imprisonment.

title: No official level discussion on donor conference yet: Official
byline: Amidst various speculations on a donor conference to raise funds for rebuilding after the Ditwah cyclone, Commissioner-General of Essential Services Prabath Chandrakeerthi said yesterday there has been no official level discussion on calling a donor conference as yet.

title: Bangladesh’s BNP wins big in first election since Gen Z uprising
byline: The Bangladesh Nationalist Party won a landslide parliamentary election on Friday, local TV stations showed, securing a resounding mandate in a pivotal vote that is expected to restore political stability in the South Asian nation.
